can you recheck the indentation of test result section
I'm happy with the indentation as it is.
i think ``` quote is not working here i guess
I'm not sure what you mean.  What is it you are looking for?

The ``` is used for markdown like below.

``` 
hello world.
```

same here also
can you check proper quote for this
What is the proper quote?  I think this is fine.
Has this been discussed at all previously?

I am not sure of previous discussions, but I have this change to start the discussion.

Maybe move to discord if more discussion is needed.
I've been waiting for discussion about what people think of this new method to be done in the PDI yaml commit.  Personally I'm OK with it but maybe people have other/better ideas.
can we add some debug msg statement before returning the empty array
eh, that feels a bit too noisy to me.

yeah, this will print a lot of errors.

Actually, should we throw an error here instead? since it doesn't meet our expectation of being associated with the associationPath.
I don't think so.  If we filter the subtree down to nothing because of the interfaces argument we don't throw an error in that case.  Isn't this the same thing?
ok, sounds good. that make sense.
eh, that feels a bit too noisy to me as well.

There are a number of places here where the PDI says "object_path" but the code here says "string".  I think this is an overall problem with the implementation here, but it'd be nice if these new methods at least matched.
That seems easy enough to fix.  Willy can you send an update for these new interfaces?
Would you be willing to add the new methods to the users guide at https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/architecture/object-mapper.md?
sure, marking as unresolved so I see this again.
Consider adding a test to verify GetAssociatedSubTree call as well
Maybe give this a different name, since it is a vector of interface pairs and not paths
nit: New line at the end file (Same for some of the other files in the change)
Will submit this after https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/60554 is also approved.
